                    "body": "<p>I think you mean this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>def zoom_at(img, x, y, zoom):\n    w, h = img.size\n    zoom2 = zoom * 2\n    img = img.crop((x - w / zoom2, y - h / zoom2, \n                    x + w / zoom2, y + h / zoom2))\n    return img.resize((w, h), Image.LANCZOS)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This will crop the image around the point where you zoom into and then upscale the resulting image to the original size. </p>\n"
                }
